rebeccasalinasart.com</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ObBzxlS</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[friendlynoodles]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>UNIONISE!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/CC4fBnW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7jHuxbZ.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/CC4fBnW</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[surprisinglynotmyrealname]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cute Badass! :)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/MtJ5nrt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VMuszNR.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Samantha Wright</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/MtJ5nrt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Luvlyquants]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>They didn't realize they left their camera on.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/659ntMS</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/x2JH5ZF.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/659ntMS</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[OctopussSevenTwo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Finally! After 30 years I’ve completed and rebuild my Black Seas Barracuda</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/siZPPod</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8ahoqQU.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It took me A LOT of work to gather all the bricks that were missing and complete this set. But I finally did it! I’ve build my LEGO Black Seas Barracuda (set 6285). 

More detailed (close-up) shots below this post

Story time: When I was 11 years old, I saved money to buy this set. I think I’ve washed a hundred cars and it also took all my birthday money but it was all worth it. This was one of my favorite sets and it still is. I’ve always kept all my childhood LEGO sets in one big box. But all the sets together has been all mixed up and I never took the effort to sort it out (so were the bricks of this set). 

Long story short: I’ve moved this big LEGO box with me ever since I was a kid, and now I finally took the time to sort all the bricks for this ship and get the ones that were missing. A lot of bricks were missing..</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hsSF47j.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Preparing with this checklist I found on internet. It helped to find back all the bricks of this set in my box of mixed LEGO. But also a lot of bricks were missing. It took me six orders to find all missing bricks and parts, using different brick stores online.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bBbg9pk.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Close up of the lower deck</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sLGN45D.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The original sails are all dirty, ragged and moldy. There was also one sail missing. After looking online for a replacement set, I decided to make sails myself out of black paper. Because even the replacement sets were very expensive.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oBqi7bq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>New black sails made out of paper. I simply traced the original sails after ironing them. I carefully used a cut out template to make clean black sails. They are a bit stiffer than the originals but they work really well and look good.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RCV456P.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Close up of the inside where the canons and cannonballs are stored. (auto focus wasn’t helping sorry for that)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ETAQZMQ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I only had three of these coins left in my box of old LEGO. But I insisted to get everything complete. And with this set also came these coins. I had to look for them online and they cost me almost €1,- per coin. So that was a bad trade.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FJO7soC.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Close up shot of my favorite character Captain Red beard and his parrot.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bXIO33M.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Close up of the upper deck details</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iRaRoXX.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The figurehead on the front of the ship</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/W69ry48.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This ship also comes with a rowing boat

Building this set was harder than I thought it would be. I learned that old instructions are much worse to work with compared to new LEGO sets. There is no brick count for every step and a lot of steps are happening on a single page. You have to triple check every page before you continue.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZWCL0S1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The yellow details look great on this. I’m also happy with how the black sails turned out. Not like the original but it fits the color scheme perfectly.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9ktkHf9.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Walking the plank. Not so fun fact: this set contains a lot of flags that are hard to find or super expensive. Especially the big pirate flag. Some of my flags have the clamps broke off. I still have to replace these one day.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PigwEPO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Set info:
Year Released: 1989
Weight: 2862g 
Item Dim.: 58 x 46.5 x 22 cm 
845 Parts
