: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ohjFz2S</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vladrichdemaclant]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>This is not what you think it is</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YVnRxQQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TRiLxCV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I see so many white supremacists using the punisher logo. Let me reiterate that if he were real he would hunt down and kill groups like the proud boys and the oath keepers. 

The punisher used to be one of my favorite heros. Now I feel like I cannot have any clothing or anything with the skull on it or I will be confused for a white supremacist.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YVnRxQQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SatanicOtaku]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Well shit</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/nhJivZv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0PYvQvZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My wife of 5 years, who I have a 3 year old with, and I have had major issues due to her mental health for years. I’ve been so warn down by her drinking and anger that I’ve finally decided enough is enough. I had plans of asking her to separate and eventually divorce this weekend after yet another horrible week with her. I support the house fully while she decided to go back to school. I got a phone call yesterday from her crying her eyes out that her mother had finally not come back from another OD. there’s a ton of back story that I won’t get into but my wife’s child hood was an absolute nightmare due to her drug addict parents. Obviously this had caused her some major lasting damage. I’ve tried so hard to help and be supportive but there’s a limit to what a person can take. I finally hit that point and now this happens. I’m just tired. I feel thin. I have to be the supportive one because there really isn’t a choice. I can’t be the worst person in the world and leave her while this is going on. I can’t do that but now I’m left to make all the arrangements and cover the cost of whatever needs to be done which I don’t have the money to do. I have no idea how I’m going to get through this in one piece. I feel selfish and angry and sad. I’ve already been sucking it up for our sons sake and trying not to be an asshole to someone who walks all over me and treats everyone around her like garbage. I thought I was going to loose my mind before this shit. Don’t do drugs people. The effects are far reaching and extremely destructive. Sorry just venting to the void. Don’t really have anyone to talk to.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nhJivZv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[therobotmd101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>That is a DAMN GOOD POINT!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RHG4IKM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zukBndo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Link to tweet:

https://twitter.com/judy577599/status/1512260262715265030?s=21&t=CsSkNflNdQc6GpBE_3wdcw</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/RHG4IKM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ridiculousbudget]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I just put down my best friend. I only hope he understands how much he was loved.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Y2mZTLk</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JMHXUIP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He loved NASCAR.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/E20VTiU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He loved taking selfies.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KngyRpF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He hated the stems of cilantro.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KyWbLhK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cuddling was his favorite.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/a8eyGFe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He wore hats. I loved those airplane ears.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VM0sRlW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Air vents were all his. Only his.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/f6j4zL1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He loved his Valentines present.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LU2YZdz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>But suddenly he didn't even want his favorite things.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/W6wyIYA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We tried everything. He was put on so many meds to try to fix him. He looked miserable.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1nQhJs0.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After so much torture and no progress, we made the hardest decision. I spent all night the night before cuddling him on the floor, watching his favorite shows.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Y2mZTLk</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[FacePalmTrees]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>a little story</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mYspYDy</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2uoRGiL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/mYspYDy</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AkitakaL]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Grinder</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Ej9rwaV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/b7ZGaND.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ej9rwaV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[minPD0309]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Day 316: of cheeseburgers I want inside of me</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/t3ZCCwl</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vzDOy5c.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Hot Mess & Cheese

