n><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FBFJaul.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It's a secret that I've kept for the past 5 years. He couldn't be there that day, so his dad and I took Toby, a 13 year old Border Collie, in to be put down. He had an inoperable tumor in his intestines and his legs weren't functioning properly anymore. We had all decided that the best thing to do for our boy was to have him put down. 

His last moments have haunted me for years. I had never had a dog put down before. I didn't know that they were supposed to give him a sedative, and that they didn't. All I know is that he died screeching at the top of his lungs, muzzled, technician holding him down, just screaming one blood curdling scream after another. I have never heard such a horrible noise from an animal. He howled until his voice broke and then finally slipped away, still trying to cry. He died looking into my FIL's eyes, begging for help that would never come. 

While we were driving home with his body, we decided that our families didn't need to know. We would tell them that he slipped away peacefully, as though he'd fallen asleep. We agreed that we would tell everyone that we don't use that vet anymore because they're too expensive, not because of what had happened. He said that he never wanted to talk about it again. He felt like he'd killed him, he said, and he wanted to try to forget. 

I've carried the secret for years, and it's been so hard not having anyone to talk to about it. 

Last week, it finally came out. We were talking about taking our 20 year old cat in soon...he's not doing well and I'm terrified of that happening to him. After a moment of shock, my husband thanked me for telling him the truth and we cried together. He promised me that we would take extra precautions with the vet to make sure that they didn't hurt him like they hurt Toby.

Having this off of my chest is such a relief. I had no idea how much better I would feel just not carrying that burden alone.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/inm2SrG</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[QuicklyAndWithPurpose]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Well, at least the CEO got theirs...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YPk8i82</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Njw6fWz.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Taken from : https://twitter.com/kenklippenstein/status/1512863326581276682</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YPk8i82</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mech0T1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>One step forward ....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BLEGBz6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DovmPiG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BLEGBz6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>To be fair, under strengths they could write &quot;Honesty&quot;</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/326jSQt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AMaJMif.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/326jSQt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Srajo101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>(Insert Ash’s speech from A L I E N here)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YU97yAe</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/diUnOEN.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>“Purrfect organism”</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YU97yAe</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GravityOtter]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Very small Parks and Rec “dump”</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/odvGd0Y</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https:/